question: The United Nations peacekeeping mission "UNMISET" was deployed in which country?
explanation: The United Nations Mission of Support to East Timor (UNMISET) was deployed in Timor-Leste, Timor-Leste is also known as East Timor, in 2002, the day East Timor became an internationally recognised independent country. This mission lasted for three years from 2002 and 2005 and it got replaced by the United Nations Office in Timor-Leste (UNOTIL).
